<TITLE> Khaleda asks party men to help the flood-hit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia Wednesday asked party followers to stand by the flood-affected people. "Now it is the main work," she told leaders and workers of Bogra in a midday teleconference organised at a free medical camp at Sariakandi Koipara flood control embankment. "I am with you. Stand by the flood-hit people with whatever you have. I have sent Hannan Shah. He will conduct relief work with BNP leaders and workers," the former prime minister said. Her adviser ASM Hannan Shah, Jatiyatabadi Jubo Dal central officer secretary Reaz Uddin, Jatiyatabadi Tanti Dal vice president Abdur Rahman Tapan and district BNP vice president Zakiullah Apel, among others, were present. "I strongly feel the urge to go to Bogra. I will go if I get a chance," Khaleda said. The BNP chief greeted all present at the camp including journalists and medical staff. "BNP is always by the side of the people. The leaders and workers of my party are by your side and will remain so," she said. Before the teleconference Hannan Shah distributed relief among the flood-affected people at Tekani Chikai Nagar union and Sariakandi Madrasa ground under Sonatala upazila in the morning. Hannan said he was distributing relief in different parts of the country under the directive of Khaleda. bdnews2
